From: Kamil Lulko <limakzagan@gmail.com>
Subject: [PARKED PROTOTYPE] FEX ARM64EC: fix x4 for variadic calls on DLL-load gap

★ Apply to external/fex-upstream, then rebuild libarm64ecfex.dll. ★

Generalizes the Hangover #225 wine workaround to ALL variadic ARM64EC entry
thunks (the compiler-generated ones the wine ndr_stubless fix cannot reach).
When emulated x86_64 calls a variadic ARM64EC function and the call lazy-loads a
DLL, FEX's ExitFunctionEC leaves x4 (the entry thunk's stack-param base = caller
original SP) 0x20 too low; a {args,len} descriptor with len==0x10 lands at x4+0x28
where the entry thunk's +0x20 shadow-space skip reads it. We detect that and undo
the gap. VALIDATED: clears the PACE pace_wrapping_fi crash and lets LDSvc.exe run
all of PACE init (5.5KB -> 3.1MB log).

⚠ PARKED — NOT shipped. Issues to harden before trusting it:
  - layout-SENSITIVE: VSTPOC_STACK_PCT (bigger stack) re-breaks it → the 0x28
    offset / gap size is not robust across stack layouts.
  - GLOBAL change to every emulated->ARM64EC call → regression risk on other
    plugins (BIAS/TONEX/…) UNVERIFIED.
  - reveals a deeper PACE crash (null-read exception loop -> INVALID_DISPOSITION
    -> stack overflow further in init).
Upstream-worthy: this is the FEX-side fix AndreRH asked for in Hangover #225 and
that nobody has written. File it with FEX to have them harden the offset.
diff --git a/Source/Windows/ARM64EC/Module.S b/Source/Windows/ARM64EC/Module.S
index 365931332..9777d0501 100644
--- a/Source/Windows/ARM64EC/Module.S
+++ b/Source/Windows/ARM64EC/Module.S
@@ -86,6 +86,19 @@ ExitFunctionSuspendResumePoint:
   ldr lr, [x4], #0x8 // Pop the return address into lr.
   mov sp, x4
 
+  // vstpoc: generalize Hangover #225 to ALL variadic entry thunks. When an
+  // x86_64->ARM64EC call lazy-loads a DLL, an extra 0x20 gap is left on the stack so
+  // x4 (= caller's original SP, the entry thunk's stack-param base) is 0x20 too low;
+  // a {args,len} descriptor whose len==0x10 sits at x4+0x28 (where the variadic entry
+  // thunk's +0x20 shadow-space skip lands). Detect that and undo the gap, so the
+  // entry thunk reads the real overflow args instead of the descriptor (fixes PACE/
+  // iLok LDSvc + the compiler-generated thunks the wine ndr_stubless fix can't reach).
+  // x16 is a free intra-procedure scratch register here.
+  ldr x16, [x4, #0x28]
+  cmp x16, #0x10
+  b.ne ret_sp_aligned
+  add x4, x4, #0x20
+
 ret_sp_aligned:
   br x17
 
